    Tesla's weakening Europe demand, Upwork rises with Q1 beat
    Josh Lipton · Host
    Tue, May 6, 2025, 10:55 AM

    In This Article:

    ^IXIC
    ^DJI
    TSLA
    ^GSPC
    UPWK

    Market Domination host Josh Lipton tracks today's top market stories in this Market Minute, including the three stock market indexes (^GSPC, ^IXIC, ^DJI) slipping ahead of the Federal Reserve's two-day May FOMC meeting..

    Tesla (TSLA) shares fall on weaker demand in Europe, with April registrations in the UK falling 62% year-over-year and 46% in Germany.

    Upwork (UPWK) shares surge after beating first quarter earnings and revenue estimates, while raising its full-year adjusted EBITDA forecast.

    Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

    00:00 Speaker A

    It's time for your finances. Market minute, stocks slip as the Fed kicks off its two-day policy meeting. Investors keep an eye on how President Trump's tariffs could influence the Fed's next move. Tesla shares under pressure as Europe remains a tough market for the EV maker. Data points to demand weakness amid a model Y changeover and CEO Elon Musk, polarizing role in the Trump administration. Latest data out of the UK found Tesla registrations falling 62% in April compared to a year earlier. Tesla's UK underperformance follows weakness in other key regions. Germany's KBA trade group reporting registrations dipping 46% in that country. Meanwhile, Upwork shares surging after topping first quarter earnings and revenue estimates. The online recruitment services company also raised its full-year forecast per just and EBITDA beating Wall Street's expectations. That's your Yahoo Finance market minute.
